  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And children, all around us, seeing this cruelty, began to scream, and generally, we were all very scared.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This one Nazi officer in front had white gloves, a white, white gloves on his hands.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in his right hand, he held a little stick or baton.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was very neatly dressed in such a dusty place in his fancy Nazi uniform, shiny black boots.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He used this little baton to separate us into three groups.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First, the men had to go one way, and the women had to go another way.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then he sent all the-- approximately all those between the ages of 16 or 17 to approximately 50 into one group, and the children, the handicapped, the sick he sent in another way, and the men went through the same thing.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So we had these different directions to go to-- basically two directions, but the men and the women separately.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so I was sent with my mother, and my sister, [NON-ENGLISH], who was 12 years old, was sent off with the children, the old and the young, the sick and the disabled.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And mother thought that [NON-ENGLISH] will be, will be well taken care of by the old people because the old people would take care of the young people, the children, maybe even cook for them, while we probably would have to work very hard, judging by the age group of our group.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- but soon-- and so we started walking in the opposite direction.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And soon after [NON-ENGLISH] was separated from us, a wagon, pulled by two horses, was catching up from behind.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
